{"timestamp":"2026-03-13T20:13:48.210Z","level":"INFO","message":"codex stdout","iteration":2,"chunk":"Implemented claim acquisition and release in [taskFile.ts](c:\\Users\\ben.jones\\source\\repos\\Ralph\\RalphDex\\ralph-codex-vscode-starter\\src\\ralph\\taskFile.ts#L51) and added focused regression coverage in [taskFile.test.ts](c:\\Users\\ben.jones\\source\\repos\\Ralph\\RalphDex\\ralph-codex-vscode-starter\\test\\taskFile.test.ts#L406). The new API uses a sibling `.lock` file on the claim file, writes the claim, re-reads it, and verifies the caller still holds the canonical active claim before returning success. Contested claims return without writing, release is idempotent, and stale active claims are surfaced via result metadata rather than auto-released.\n\nValidation: `npm run compile:tests` passed. A direct run of `node --require ./test/register-vscode-stub.cjs ./out-test/test/taskFile.test.js` passed all 20 tests, including the new claim cases. The repo-level `npm test` did not complete in this sandbox because Node’s test runner was blocked from spawning subprocesses with `EPERM`; that failure affected every suite uniformly, not just this change.\n\nAssumption: I added `claimFilePath` as the first parameter to `acquireClaim` and `releaseClaim` so the API can operate on a durable file-backed claim ledger now, without inventing hidden global path resolution. Follow-up work remains in later T24 items: wiring this into iteration selection/reconciliation, surfacing claim diagnostics in preflight/status, and potentially consolidating the locking helper with the future `withTaskFileLock` path.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"selectedTaskId\": \"T24.1.2\",\n  \"requestedStatus\": \"done\",\n  \"progressNote\": \"Implemented file-backed claim acquisition and release in taskFile.ts with sibling lock-file coordination, write-then-verify canonical holder checks, contested/no-write behavior, idempotent release, and stale-claim detection metadata. Added focused taskFile tests covering acquire, contention, idempotence, and stale claims.\",\n  \"validationRan\": \"cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run compile:tests; node --require ./test/register-vscode-stub.cjs ./out-test/test/taskFile.test.js\",\n  \"needsHumanReview\": false\n}\n```\n"}
