{"timestamp":"2026-03-13T20:21:36.950Z","level":"WARN","message":"codex stderr","iteration":2,"chunk":"codex\nChanged [taskFile.ts](/c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/src/ralph/taskFile.ts#L1291) so `releaseClaim` now only releases the canonical active claim for a task. If another agent is the current holder, it returns `not_held` without rewriting the claim file. That keeps release behavior aligned with the same canonical-holder model used by `acquireClaim`.\n\nAdded regressions in [taskFile.test.ts](/c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/taskFile.test.ts#L477) and [taskFile.test.ts](/c:/Users/ben.jones/source/repos/Ralph/RalphDex/ralph-codex-vscode-starter/test/taskFile.test.ts#L511) to cover:\n- non-holder release attempts leaving the file unchanged\n- duplicate active claims from the same agent releasing only the canonical one\n\nValidation: `npm run compile:tests` passed. `npm test` failed in this sandbox before executing tests because Node’s test runner could not spawn workers (`spawn EPERM`), and the focused fallback `node --require ./test/register-vscode-stub.cjs --test --test-concurrency=1 ./out-test/test/taskFile.test.js` hit the same environment restriction.\n\nAssumption: release semantics should apply only to the canonical holder, not any matching historical or non-canonical active claim. Limitation: I could not execute the test suite end-to-end in this environment because process spawning is blocked.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"selectedTaskId\": \"T24.1.2\",\n  \"requestedStatus\": \"done\",\n  \"progressNote\": \"Tightened task claim release semantics so only the canonical active holder can release a claim, and added regression coverage for non-holder and duplicate-claim cases.\",\n  \"validationRan\": \"cd ralph-codex-vscode-starter && npm run compile:tests; npm test (blocked by sandbox spawn EPERM); node --require ./test/register-vscode-stub.cjs --test --test-concurrency=1 ./out